A 35-year-old man died from multiple bullet wounds   following a  shooting in Walmer Township on Tuesday afternoon. Police spokesperson Colonel Priscilla Naidu said Walmer police officers received a complaint at  about 3.30pm of a shooting in Goniwe Street. “Upon arrival, they found the body of a man, aged 35,  lying in the street. “He  had multiple bullet wounds all over his body,” Naidu said. The motive for the shooting is unknown. The man’s name is being  withheld until his next of kin have been notified of his death. HeraldLIVE